</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-37_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">Legislation, regulations, and best practices</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-41_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In accordance with the Health and Safety (First Aid) Regulations 1981, employers have a legal obligation to provide adequate first aid training and resources in the workplace. Guidelines from organisations like the Resuscitation Council UK and the Health and Safety Executive offer valuable insights into best practices for managing nosebleeds effectively.


<br>

