</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-50_ pf-text-1"><strong>Positioning</strong> - Instruct the person to lean forward slightly to prevent blood from flowing down the throat, reducing the risk of aspiration.












</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-52_ pf-text-1"><strong>Apply pressure </strong>- Pinch the soft part of the nose (just below the bridge) with your thumb and index finger, applying firm pressure for 10-15 minutes.











</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-54_ pf-text-1"><strong>Cold compress </strong>- Placing a cold compress or ice pack on the bridge of the nose can help constrict blood vessels and minimise bleeding.












</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-56_ pf-text-1"><strong>Seek medical assistance</strong> - If bleeding persists after 15 minutes of continuous pressure or if the nosebleed is severe, seek medical attention promptly.













